    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Moses",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "God reveals Himself to Moses\u2014Moses is transfigured\u2014He is confronted by Satan\u2014Moses sees many inhabited worlds\u2014Worlds without number were created by the Son\u2014God's work and glory is to bring to pass the immortality and eternal life of man.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The words of God, which he spake unto Moses at a time when Moses was caught up into an exceedingly high mountain,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 12:30; Moses 1:42.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 19:3; Ezek. 40:2; Rev. 21:10; Moses 1:42.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he saw God face to face, and he talked with him, and the glory of God was upon Moses; therefore Moses could endure his presence.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 3:6; 33:20 (11\u201323); John 1:18; Ether 3:15; Moses 1:11. TG\u00a0God, Privilege of Seeing; Jesus Christ, Appearances, Antemortal; Vision.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 12:8; Deut. 34:10; D&C 17:1. TG\u00a0God, Manifestations of.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 25:1. TG\u00a0Communication.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 5:24; Moses 1:14 (13\u201314, 25). TG\u00a0Glory; God, Glory of; Transfiguration.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And God spake unto Moses, saying: Behold, I am the Lord God Almighty, and Endless is my name; for I am without beginning of days or end of years; and is not this endless?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 19:6. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Power of.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 68
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 63:16; D&C 19:10 (9\u201312); Moses 7:35. TG\u00a0God, Eternal Nature of.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 3:15.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And, behold, thou art my son; wherefore look, and I will show thee the workmanship of mine hands; but not all, for my works are without end, and also my words, for they never cease.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 7:4.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 9:12.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 7:32 (32\u201337).",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 40:5; 92:5; Morm. 9:16 (16\u201320); D&C 76:114. TG\u00a0God, Power of.",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 111:8 (7\u20138); 1\u00a0Ne. 14:7; D&C 29:33; Moses 1:38.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 139
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 33:11; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:16; D&C 1:38 (37\u201339).",
                        "start": 153,
                        "end": 158
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, no man can behold all my works, except he behold all my glory; and no man can behold all my glory, and afterwards remain in the flesh on the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Works of.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory; Jesus Christ, Glory of.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Privilege of Seeing.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 24:17; John 12:41. TG\u00a0Celestial Glory.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I have a work for thee, Moses, my son; and thou art in the similitude of mine Only Begotten; and mine Only Begotten is and shall be the Savior, for he is full of grace and truth; but there is no God beside me, and all things are present with me, for I know them all.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 1:26; Deut. 18:15; Acts 3:22; 1\u00a0Ne. 22:21; Moses 1:16 (13\u201316).",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:33.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 6:57.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 13:40. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Savior.",
                        "start": 140,
                        "end": 146
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 1:17 (14, 17); 2\u00a0Ne. 2:6; Alma 13:9. TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 166,
                        "end": 171
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:7.",
                        "start": 176,
                        "end": 181
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 32:17; 1\u00a0Kgs. 8:60; Isa. 44:8; 45:5 (5\u201322); 46:9.",
                        "start": 196,
                        "end": 198
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 48:3 (3\u20137); 1\u00a0Ne. 9:6; Moses 1:35. TG\u00a0God, Foreknowledge of; God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 256,
                        "end": 260
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 2
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, behold, this one thing I show unto thee, Moses, my son, for thou art in the world, and now I show it unto thee.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Moses looked, and beheld the world upon which he was created; and Moses beheld the world and the ends thereof, and all the children of men which are, and which were created; of the same he greatly marveled and wondered.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 2:1.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:27.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 103
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 8:3 (3\u20134).",
                        "start": 222,
                        "end": 230
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the presence of God withdrew from Moses, that his glory was not upon Moses; and Moses was left unto himself. And as he was left unto himself, he fell unto the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 10:12.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 6:5; Acts 9:4; JS\u2014H 1:20.",
                        "start": 149,
                        "end": 153
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that it was for the space of many hours before Moses did again receive his natural strength like unto man; and he said unto himself: Now, for this cause I know that man is nothing, which thing I never had supposed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dan. 10:8 (8, 17); 1\u00a0Ne. 17:47; 19:20; Alma 27:17.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 111
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mortality.",
                        "start": 185,
                        "end": 188
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 42:6 (1\u20136); Dan. 4:35; Hel. 12:7; Ether 3:2. TG\u00a0Humility.",
                        "start": 192,
                        "end": 199
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But now mine own eyes have beheld God; but not my natural, but my spiritual eyes, for my natural eyes could not have beheld; for I should have withered and died in his presence; but his glory was upon me; and I beheld his face, for I was transfigured before him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:2. TG\u00a0God, Privilege of Seeing.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 6:36.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:31.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 33:20.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 67:10 (10\u201313).",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 123
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 19:21; D&C 67:11 (11\u201313).",
                        "start": 143,
                        "end": 151
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 20:19.",
                        "start": 156,
                        "end": 160
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 186,
                        "end": 191
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 32:30; Moses 7:4.",
                        "start": 222,
                        "end": 226
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 17:2 (1\u20138); D&C 137:1. TG\u00a0Transfiguration.",
                        "start": 238,
                        "end": 250
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that when Moses had said these words, behold, Satan came tempting him, saying: Moses, son of man, worship me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 4:4 (1, 4). TG\u00a0Devil.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 4:2 (1\u201313); 2\u00a0Cor. 11:14 (13\u201315); Rev. 12:9 (7\u20139); 2\u00a0Ne. 1:18 (17\u201318); Moses 1:21; 6:49.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Moses looked upon Satan and said: Who art thou? For behold, I am a son of God, in the similitude of his Only Begotten; and where is thy glory, that I should worship thee?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 1:6; Isa. 14:12 (12\u201315).",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 95
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 88:24.",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 166
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For behold, I could not look upon God, except his glory should come upon me, and I were transfigured before him. But I can look upon thee in the natural man. Is it not so, surely?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:2 (2, 25). TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 1:17.",
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Blessed be the name of my God, for his Spirit hath not altogether withdrawn from me, or else where is thy glory, for it is darkness unto me? And I can judge between thee and God; for God said unto me: Worship God, for him only shalt thou serve.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 4:10. TG\u00a0Worship.",
                        "start": 201,
                        "end": 208
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 7:3; 3\u00a0Ne. 13:24.",
                        "start": 238,
                        "end": 243
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Get thee hence, Satan; deceive me not; for God said unto me: Thou art after the similitude of mine Only Begotten.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:6. TG\u00a0God, Body of, Corporeal Nature.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he also gave me commandments when he called unto me out of the burning bush, saying: Call upon God in the name of mine Only Begotten, and worship me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 19:3.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 3:2 (2\u201315).",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:8.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And again Moses said: I will not cease to call upon God, I have other things to inquire of him: for his glory has been upon me, wherefore I can judge between him and thee. Depart hence, Satan.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory; Jesus Christ, Glory of.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 109
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 4:10.",
                        "start": 172,
                        "end": 178
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 3
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, when Moses had said these words, Satan cried with a loud voice, and ranted upon the earth, and commanded, saying: I am the Only Begotten, worship me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0False Christs.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014M 1:6 (5\u20139).",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 145
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Moses began to fear exceedingly; and as he began to fear, he saw the bitterness of hell. Nevertheless, calling upon God, he received strength, and he commanded, saying: Depart from me, Satan, for this one God only will I worship, which is the God of glory.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Fearful.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:47 (44\u201347). TG\u00a0Hell.",
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JS\u2014H 1:16 (15\u201316). TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 135
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Power of; Strength.",
                        "start": 158,
                        "end": 166
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 275,
                        "end": 280
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now Satan began to tremble, and the earth shook; and Moses received strength, and called upon God, saying: In the name of the Only Begotten, depart hence, Satan.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:12.",
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 151
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 10:1. TG\u00a0Spirits, Evil or Unclean.",
                        "start": 159,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Satan cried with a loud voice, with weeping, and wailing, and gnashing of teeth; and he departed hence, even from the presence of Moses, that he beheld him not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 13:42 (41\u201342); Mosiah 16:2 (1\u20133).",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now of this thing Moses bore record; but because of wickedness it is not had among the children of men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 11:52. TG\u00a0Record Keeping.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:41.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that when Satan had departed from the presence of Moses, that Moses lifted up his eyes unto heaven, being filled with the Holy Ghost, which beareth record of the Father and the Son;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 11:32 (32, 36); Moses 8:24.",
                        "start": 142,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And calling upon the name of God, he beheld his glory again, for it was upon him; and he heard a voice, saying: Blessed art thou, Moses, for I, the Almighty, have chosen thee, and thou shalt be made stronger than many waters; for they shall obey thy command as if thou wert God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 5:30; 3\u00a0Ne. 11:3.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Abr. 3:23.",
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 169
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 14:21.",
                        "start": 218,
                        "end": 224
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Priesthood, Authority.",
                        "start": 250,
                        "end": 257
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 4:16.",
                        "start": 274,
                        "end": 277
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And lo, I am with thee, even unto the end of thy days; for thou shalt deliver my people from bondage, even Israel my chosen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 3:10 (7\u201312). TG\u00a0Israel, Deliverance of.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 20:2; Ps. 80:8; 1\u00a0Ne. 17:23 (23\u201325). TG\u00a0Israel, Bondage of, in Egypt.",
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 8:53 (51, 53). TG\u00a0Israel, Twelve Tribes of.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 113
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 33:12.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass, as the voice was still speaking, Moses cast his eyes and beheld the earth, yea, even all of it; and there was not a particle of it which he did not behold, discerning it by the Spirit of God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 88:47 (45\u201347); Moses 1:8; 7:23; Abr. 3:21 (21\u201323). TG\u00a0Vision.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Discernment, Spiritual; Holy Ghost, Mission of.",
                        "start": 177,
                        "end": 187
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Spirit of.",
                        "start": 198,
                        "end": 204
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he beheld also the inhabitants thereof, and there was not a soul which he beheld not; and he discerned them by the Spirit of God; and their numbers were great, even numberless as the sand upon the sea shore.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 7:23.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he beheld many lands; and each land was called earth, and there were inhabitants on the face thereof.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 1:10. TG\u00a0Earth, Dividing of.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 17:36.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Moses called upon God, saying: Tell me, I pray thee, why these things are so, and by what thou madest them?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 2:1.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And behold, the glory of the Lord was upon Moses, so that Moses stood in the presence of God, and talked with him face to face. And the Lord God said unto Moses: For mine own purpose have I made these things. Here is wisdom and it remaineth in me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 5:4; Moses 1:11.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 126
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 45:18 (17\u201318); Eph. 3:11 (7\u201312); 2\u00a0Ne. 2:15 (14\u201330). TG\u00a0Earth, Purpose of.",
                        "start": 175,
                        "end": 182
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Intelligence of.",
                        "start": 217,
                        "end": 223
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p31",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 4
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And by the word of my power, have I created them, which is mine Only Begotten Son, who is full of grace and truth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 1:3 (1\u20134); Heb. 1:2 (1\u20133); Rev. 19:13 (13\u201315); Jacob 4:9; Moses 2:1 (1, 5). TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:7 (7\u20138). TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And worlds without number have I created; and I also created them for mine own purpose; and by the Son I created them, which is mine Only Begotten.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 9:9 (7\u20139); Ps. 8:3 (3\u20134); Amos 9:6; D&C 76:24; Moses 7:30 (29\u201331). TG\u00a0Astronomy; Creation; God, Works of; World.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Creator.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship; Jesus Christ, Jehovah.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Creator.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:6.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 146
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the first man of all men have I called Adam, which is many.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 3:7.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Abr. 1:3. TG\u00a0Adam.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 15:45 (45\u201348); 2\u00a0Ne. 2:20 (19\u201320); D&C 27:11; 76:24; 138:38; Moses 4:26; 6:9.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But only an account of this earth, and the inhabitants thereof, give I unto you. For behold, there are many worlds that have passed away by the word of my power. And there are many that now stand, and innumerable are they unto man; but all things are numbered unto me, for they are mine and I know them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:6; D&C 38:2; 88:41; Moses 1:6; 7:36; Abr. 3:2 (1\u201316). TG\u00a0God, Omniscience of.",
                        "start": 293,
                        "end": 297
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Moses spake unto the Lord, saying: Be merciful unto thy servant, O God, and tell me concerning this earth, and the inhabitants thereof, and also the heavens, and then thy servant will be content.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 2:1.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God spake unto Moses, saying: The heavens, they are many, and they cannot be numbered unto man; but they are numbered unto me, for they are mine.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 1:1; Moses 2:1; Abr. 4:1. TG\u00a0Heaven.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And as one earth shall pass away, and the heavens thereof even so shall another come; and there is no end to my works, neither to my words.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:4.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 105
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For behold, this is my work and my glory\u2014to bring to pass the immortality and eternal life of man.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 90:16; Matt. 5:48; Rom. 8:17 (14\u201321); 2\u00a0Ne. 2:15 (14\u201330); Alma 42:26; D&C 29:43 (42\u201344). TG\u00a0God, Works of.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Micah 2:9; Mosiah 4:12; D&C 81:4 (3\u20134). TG\u00a0Glory; Jesus Christ, Glory of.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 6:59. TG\u00a0Immortality; Jesus Christ, Mission of; Resurrection.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Eternal Life; Man, Potential to Become like Heavenly Father.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Purpose of.",
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now, Moses, my son, I will speak unto thee concerning this earth upon which thou standest; and thou shalt write the things which I shall speak.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Neh. 13:1 (1\u20133); 2\u00a0Tim. 3:16; 2\u00a0Ne. 29:11 (11\u201312).",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And in a day when the children of men shall esteem my words as naught and take many of them from the book which thou shalt write, behold, I will raise up another like unto thee; and they shall be had again among the children of men\u2014among as many as shall believe.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:23.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 13:26 (23\u201332).",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 78
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 17:14; 1\u00a0Ne. 5:11; 19:23.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 105
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 3:9 (7\u201319).",
                        "start": 162,
                        "end": 166
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 13:32, 39\u201340; D&C 9:2.",
                        "start": 196,
                        "end": 199
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "(These words were spoken unto Moses in the mount, the name of which shall not be known among the children of men. And now they are spoken unto you. Show them not unto any except them that believe. Even so. Amen.)",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:1.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
